The paper discusses sequential decision problems and metalevel decision procedures for selecting which action sequences to simulate. This topic falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), which are covered by the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The paper also uses game theory concepts, which are covered by the cs.GT sub-category. The paper also discusses Monte Carlo selection problems, which are related to computational statistics and data analysis, covered by the cs.DS sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses heuristic approximations, which are related to software engineering and programming, covered by the cs.SE sub-category.
